SIMPLE: pestle
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: pestle
<hw>pes"tle</hw> <pr>(p⟦ecr⟧s"t'l <it>or</it> p⟦ecr⟧s"'l; 277)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>pestel</ets>, OF. <ets>pestel</ets>, LL.
<ets>pestellum</ets>, L. <ets>pistillum</ets>, <ets>pistillus</ets>, a
pounder, pestle, fr. <ets>pisere</ets>, <ets>pinsere</ets>, to pound,
crush, akin to Gr. <grk>pti`ssein</grk>, Skr. <ets>pish</ets>. Cf.
<er>Pistil</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An implement for pounding and
breaking or braying substances in a mortar; <as>as, to grind with a
mortar and <ex>pestle</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A constable's or bailiff's staff; -- so called from
its shape.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chapman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The leg and leg bone of an animal, especially of a
pig; <as>as, a <ex>pestle</ex> of pork</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>pestle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: pestle
<hw>pes"tle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t. & i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Pestled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Pestling</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <def>To pound,
pulverize, bray, or mix with a pestle, or as with a pestle; to use a
pestle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>pesto</ent>⟦br⟧
